  "prompt": "Will 8 RAC tickets that have changed to CNF, get adjacent berths?",
  "response": "When 8 RAC (Reservation Against Cancellation) tickets are converted to CNF (Confirmed), it does not guarantee that the passengers will be allocated adjacent berths. The allocation of berths is determined by the available seating arrangements and the train's booking system. While efforts are made to provide adjacent seats to passengers traveling together, it ultimately depends on the specific situation, such as the layout of the coach and the overall demand for seats. It's advisable to check with the railway authorities or the ticket booking platform for specific queries regarding seat allocation.",
